title: For Sale:  H&R Model 999 Sportsman .22LR revolver
postcontent:
This is a Harrington & Richardson (H&R) Model 999 Sportsman .22LR top-break 9-shot revolver.  The H&R handgun line has long been discontinued and this particular model was their top-of-the-line .22LR revolver.  The 999 Sportsman has become quite a collector's item and my research on the Gunbroker auction site shows that they have been sold for a low of $250+ in poor condition with missing parts, up to a high of $750+ in like-new condition.  I would rate this particular one as excellent condition.  It is in perfect working condition with all original parts (no missing parts).  The serial numbers on the frame, cylinder, barrel, and rear sight all match.  The serial number prefix on this one is "AY", which according to my research, corresponds to a manufacture year of 1982.  

This revolver has been cleaned, lubed, and is ready to either be fired or stored.  I can provide additional photographs if requested.  My asking price is $500 cash, face-to-face in the north Dallas area.  I might also be open to trading depending on what you have to offer.  I'm more of a shooter than a collector, and I prefer 9mm pistols, but I'm open to all other offers.

title: Want To Buy:  J.C. Higgins 10316 bolt action or Marlin Model 80 or Ranger Model 36
postcontent:
Looking for a J.C. Higgins 10316 or a Marlin Model 80.
The Higgins is a magazine fed, bolt-action rifle. 

J.C .Higgins is a company that produced sporting goods for Sears many years ago.  This particular model has the inscription ”Sears, Roebuck & Company S, L, LR”. The latter means that it fires .22 short, long and long rifle cartridges, which is nice even though short and long are relatively hard to find.  Further research shows that it’s a copy of the Marlin Model 80. It wasn’t uncommon for big box retailers to contract gun makers to produce store-brand guns.

Ranger Model 36 -  this rifle was made by Marlin between 1934-1939 for Sears and Roebuck.

I ask that the rifle be in usable condition.

The new Epiphany Outdoor Gear Pocket Bellows "Weatherproof" Fire Starting Kit is an ancient fire starting technology molded into a modern telescopic hand tool. Unlike other fire starting kits that leave you high & dry in wet conditions, this kit provides you with:

V3 Pocket Bellows
Extending to 20" and collapsing to 3.5", Pocket Bellows compresses and focuses oxygen into the heart of a fire. The byproduct of this extra oxygen is extra heat which is the key to overcoming wet firewood.

The 100% organically waterproofed, easily ignitable, long burning cotton tinder knit come 8 to a pack. When ignited with a flint striker, match, or lighter, Fire Fuses produce a 3"-5" fire starting flame for up to 5 full minutes.

A fail proof ignition source that produces a shower of fiery hot embers in a weather condition, EZ Ignite will produce a tall flame in one strike every time when coupled with Fire Fuses and also works great on forest floor tinders.
